s, we favor a powering mechanism where the SN ejecta are\ninteracting with a dense CSM. The progenitor of OGLE-2014-SN-131 was likely a\nWolf-Rayet star with a mass greater than that of a typical SN Ibn progenitor,\nwhich expelled the CSM that the SN is interacting with.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Mar 2017 20:25:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-06-23"}
